          },
          "pause": true,
          "displayType": "poster",
          "buttonOnMobile": false,
          "label": "<p>Which layer of the epidermis contains Langerhans cells responsible for immune su</p>",
          "x": 30,
          "y": 30,
          "width": 40,
          "height": 25,
          "libraryTitle": "Multiple Choice",
          "action": {
            "library": "H5P.MultiChoice 1.16",
            "params": {
              "question": "<p>Which layer of the epidermis contains Langerhans cells responsible for immune surveillance?</p>",
              "answers": [
                {
                  "text": "<div>Stratum basale</div>",
                  "correct": false,
                  "tipsAndFeedback": {
                    "tip": "",
                    "chosenFeedback": "<div>The stratum basale is the deepest layer, containing stem cells and melanocytes attached to the basement membrane. Langerhans cells reside one layer superficial to this.</div>",
                    "notChosenFeedback": ""
                  }
                },
                {
                  "text": "<div>Stratum spinosum</div>",
                  "correct": true,
                  "tipsAndFeedback": {
                    "tip": "",
                    "chosenFeedback": "<div>Correct. The stratum spinosum houses prickle cells linked by desmosomes and Langerhans cells — antigen-presenting dendritic cells that provide the skin's first line of immune defence.</div>",
                    "notChosenFeedback": ""
                  }
                },
                {
                  "text": "<div>Stratum granulosum</div>",
                  "correct": false,
                  "tipsAndFeedback": {
                    "tip": "",
                    "chosenFeedback": "<div>The stratum granulosum contains keratohyalin granules and lamellar bodies that establish the waterproof barrier, not the immune-surveillance cells.</div>",
                    "notChosenFeedback": ""
                  }
                },
                {
                  "text": "<div>Stratum corneum</div>",
                  "correct": false,
                  "tipsAndFeedback": {
                    "tip": "",
                    "chosenFeedback": "<div>The stratum corneum consists of flat, dead, keratin-filled cells forming the physical barrier. No living immune cells are present in this outermost layer.</div>",
                    "notChosenFeedback": ""
                  }
                }
              ],
              "overallFeedback": [
                {
                  "from": 0,
                  "to": 50,
                  "feedback": "Recall the mnemonic 'Come, Let's Get Sun-Burned' — the stratum spinosum (S for Sun) houses both prickle cells and Langerhans cells for immune surveillance."
                },
                {
                  "from": 51,
                  "to": 100,
                  "feedback": "Correct! Langerhans cells reside in the stratum spinosum alongside the desmosome-linked prickle cells."
                }
              ],
              "behaviour": {
